gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 146, Knicks 122
gameRecap.excerpt: Giannis Antetokounmpo leads the way with 35 points, eight rebounds and 10 assists as the Bucks defeat the Knicks, 146-122 and advance to the IST Semifinals. Damian Lillard added 28 points, seven assists and five 3PM in the victory, while Julius Randle tallied a season-high 41 points (14-19 FG), along with six rebounds and five assists for the Knicks in the losing effort. The Bucks improve to 15-6 on the season, while the Knicks fall to 12-8.
